From: Takeshi Kihara <takeshi.kihara.df@renesas.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Feb 2017 20:26:36 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 1768/2066] arm64: dts: r8a7795-salvator-xs: Add I2C ch2
 device and pins support

This patch adds I2C ch2 devices and its pinctrl support for Salvator-X
2nd version board on R8A7795 ES2.0 SoC.

The default I2C bus clock rate of I2C ch2 sets 100 kHz. The following
I2C device on the board is connected to I2C ch2:

    AK4613, CS2000-CP

Signed-off-by: Takeshi Kihara <takeshi.kihara.df@renesas.com>
[zou:Original patch taken from
git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/horms/renesas-bsp.git
 v4.9/rcar-3.5.1]
Signed-off-by: zou cao <cao.zou@windriver.com>
---
 .../arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-xs.dts |   14 ++++++++++++++
 1 files changed, 14 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-xs.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-xs.dts
index 7b93615..d5317c8 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-xs.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-xs.dts
@@ -121,6 +121,11 @@
 		function = "hscif1";
 	};
 
+	i2c2_pins: i2c2 {
+		groups = "i2c2_a";
+		function = "i2c2";
+	};
+
 	avb_pins: avb {
 		groups = "avb_mdc";
 		function = "avb";
@@ -197,6 +202,15 @@
 	/* status = "okay"; */
 };
 
+&i2c2 {
+	pinctrl-0 = <&i2c2_pins>;
+	pinctrl-names = "default";
+
+	status = "okay";
+
+	clock-frequency = <100000>;
+};
+
 &avb {
 	pinctrl-0 = <&avb_pins>;
 	pinctrl-names = "default";
